  FIX 3: Home Page: Trip Readiness Bar
  Started: Fri Jun 26 08:37:52 EDT 2026
══════════════════════════════════════════════════
Done. Here's what changed:

**Updated `OverviewTab` — Trip Readiness section** (below the widget tiles grid):

| Criterion | Logic |
|---|---|
| **Crew confirmed** | `members.length >= 2` |
| **Packing list complete** | All meal grocery items have `got: true` (at least one must exist) |
| **Costs settled** | If dues enabled: all members `duesPaid`; otherwise: at least one shared expense logged |
| **Itinerary planned** | `events.length >= 1` |
| **Waypoints added** | At least one trail entry has `lat`/`lng` set |

**UI changes:**
- Pending items now show an amber warning triangle instead of an empty dot — clearer signal for what's still needed
- Complete items keep the existing ember-green checkmark dot
- Progress bar and `pct%` label remain, now calculated over 5 criteria instead of 4

All data flows directly from the Firestore-synced trip object — no extra user input needed.
